BEAUSOLEIL, France - Three-time Tour de France winner Chris Froome was the victim of apparent road rage on Tuesday morning.The 31-year-old Kenyan-born cyclist tweeted that he was cycling when a driver rammed his bicycle onto a pavement. He didn't appear to have been hurt, but said that his bike had been "totaled". Just got rammed on purpose by an impatient driver who followed me onto the pavement! Thankfully I'm okay -- Bike totaled. Driver kept going! pic.twitter.com/o7FT4iXsAo eNCA